<%# Scenario: morph/status-flip — Turbo 8 idiomorph target (PAT-04 empirical).
    The activate action responds with turbo_stream.replace method: :morph,
    so idiomorph patches this element's `class` attribute AND its text content
    in place without swapping the node itself. DOM identity is preserved,
    which is the PAT-04 signal: the mutation records are `attributes` and
    `characterData` on the same node, not a `childList` swap on the parent. %>
<div id="morph-status" class="<%= active ? "active" : "idle" %>">
  Active: <%= active %>
</div>
